    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_23131_1825_07_page01.jpg"/>
                
                <opener> <note>26</note>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Sussex-Place-24_ENK">24 Sussex Place</placeName>
                        Sunday morning</dateline>
                 
                </opener>
                <p>
                    
               
                    Dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Miss Edgeworth</persName> <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MurrJ1">Mr Murray</persName><lb/>
                    hearing me laud your friends<lb/>
                    My review of I Promessi Sposi<lb/>
                    insisted on having it to read<lb/>
                    and I trust he has already<lb/>
                    forwarded it to you. I was<lb/>
                    very much pleased with it<lb/>
                    indeed — one sentence about<lb/>
                    things being weeds &amp; stones to<lb/>
                    the unitiated &amp; specimens to<lb/>
                    others struck me as quite exquisite<lb/>
                    — but after so great a lapse<lb/>
                 
                    <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_23131_1825_07_page02.jpg"/>
                    
                    
                    of time it w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> never suit the<lb/>
                    Quarterley to bestow a considerable<lb/>
                    space formally on <persName ref="./Personography.xml#ManzA1">Manzoni's</persName><lb/>
                    novel — which by the bye has<lb/>
                    been translated into English<lb/>
                    some two years ago.<lb/></p>
                <p>
                    It wd give me great<lb/>
                    pleasure to receive your<lb/>
                    accomplished friends assistance<lb/>
                    W respect to some <hi rend="underline">new</hi> book<lb/>
                    and if she permit me I<lb/>
                        
                    <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_23131_1825_07_page03.jpg"/>
                    
                    <note>27</note>
                    will presently hazard such<lb/>
                    an application. Meantime<lb/>
                    pray say something proper<lb/>
                    in my name &amp; believe me<lb/></p>
                   <closer>yours, as well as her much<lb/>
                    obliged Servant<lb/>
                    <hi rend="underline"><persName ref="./Personography.xml#LockJ1">J G Lockhart</persName></hi><lb/></closer>
                     
                    <pb n="4" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_23131_1825_07_page04.jpg"/>
                    
             
                    
                <note>Sir W Scott<lb/>
                    July 1825<lb/>
                    at <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworthstown</placeName> July 1825<lb/>
                    <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeauH1">Honora</persName><lb/></note>
                
            </div>
        </body>
